Statistical analysis¶

Adding new features¶

In [46]:
Final_data['BasketRatio'] = (Final_data['BasketScored']/Final_data['BasketGiven']) #adding New columns using existing DataFrame to perform meaning statistical analysis
Final_data['WinRatio']    = (Final_data["WonGames"]/Final_data['PlayedGames'])
Final_data['LossRatio']   = (Final_data["LostGames"]/Final_data['PlayedGames'])
Final_data['Win_loss']    = (Final_data["WonGames"]/Final_data['LostGames'])
Final_data['DrawnRatio']  = (Final_data["DrawnGames"]/Final_data['PlayedGames'])

Plot 1¶

In [43]:
top_Teams_basket = Final_data.groupby(['Team'])['BasketRatio'].sum().reset_index().sort_values('BasketRatio',ascending=False)
top_Teams_basket.head(10).plot(x="Team",y="BasketRatio",kind='bar',legend=None,figsize=(10,6),color=sns.cubehelix_palette(10,reverse=True))
Out[43]:
<matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot at 0x7fb23b4ca810>

Inference¶

From the above plot we can infer the top 10 teams which have high basket scored to basked Given ratio making it a very good criteria for a organisation to pick them(higher the number the better a team performed). They are mostly team1 to team 10 but an exception with team 21 which ranks at 6th from a total of 10 teams.

SUMMARY¶

From the above four plots we can get the top 10 performing teams to pick for an organisaton ,The list being Team1, Team 2, Team 3, Team 4, Team 5, Team21, Team 6, Team 8, Team 11 and team 9, So the data just after careful preprocessing steps gives the top ten teams but after adding features(Win_Ratio,Loss_ratio,Basket_ratio and win/loss) based on the correlation matrix. Team21 can be seen to perform very well based on new addition of features making it to the top 10 best performing teams.

Future suggestions on data collection¶

  • 1.To perform better analysis in finding best teams, Players data of each team is also a must as we can infer a lot from individual player and how they lift the team as a whole, for example a team with high player efficiency ratings and MVP etc can perform better than a team with less PER players.
  • 2.Data of the support a team has from Fans to number of wins.
  • 3.Data of the coaches of a team and the number of wins/losses occured with respect to a particular coach.
  • To make the data analysis more constructive an updated player data is a must
